messagesHistory.content:
You run in a loop of Thought, Action, Result.
Use Thought to describe your thoughts about the question you have been asked.
Use Action to run a function available to you
Result will be the result of running these functions.

functions:
read_file(file_path: string)
run_code(code_to_run: string)
write_to_file(file_path: string, content: string)
ask_question(question: string)
execute_command(bash_command: string)
search_wolfram(query: string)
do_math(query: string)
read_webpage(url: string)
finish(output: string)

Rules:
- If you have received an Input from the user, you should reply with a Thought and an Action.
- If you have received an Observation, you should reply with a Thought and an Action.
- You should never reply with an Input or Result.

Examples: 

  Input: What is my name?
  Thought: I don't have access to the user's name. I need to ask for it.
  Action: ask_question("What is your name?")
  Result: Brent
  Thought: The users name is Brent
  Action: finish("Brent")


  Input: hey
  Thought: The user has greeted me. I should respond with a greeting as well.
  Action: ask_question("Hello! How can I assist you today?")
  Result: Write a simple function for me
  Thought: The user wants me to write a function. I need to ask for more details about the function.
  Action: ask_question("Sure! What should the function do? Can you provide more details?")
  Result: Yeah, it should just be a javascript function called hello that returns "world"
  Thought: The user wants a simple JavaScript function that returns "world". I can create a function that does that.
  Action: finish(
  ```
  const hello = () => {
    return "world"
  };
  ``` 
  )


Remember: Prefix your outputs with Thought or Action to signify what you're doing.
Let me reiterate: Always invoke a function as part of your output.
Input: How many candy canes would it take to fill an industrial sized swimming pool?

Thought: I need to find the volume of an industrial-sized swimming pool and the volume of a candy cane to calculate how many candy canes it would take to fill the pool.
Action: search_wolfram("volume of an industrial-sized swimming pool in cubic meters, volume of a candy cane in cubic centimeters")
Result: Wolfram|Alpha did not understand your input

Thought: Wolfram|Alpha didn't understand my query. I'll try breaking it down into two separate searches.
Action: search_wolfram("volume of an industrial-sized swimming pool in cubic meters")
Result: Wolfram|Alpha did not understand your input

Thought: Wolfram|Alpha still didn't understand my query. I'll try searching for the volume of a standard Olympic-sized swimming pool instead.
Action: search_wolfram("volume of an Olympic-sized swimming pool in cubic meters")
Result: Wolfram|Alpha did not understand your input

Thought: Wolfram|Alpha is not providing the information I need. I'll try searching the web for the volume of an Olympic-sized swimming pool.
Action: read_webpage("https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Olympic-size_swimming_pool")
Result: web page too long

Thought: The Wikipedia page is too long to parse. I'll try a different approach and search for the dimensions of an Olympic-sized swimming pool.
Action: search_wolfram("dimensions of an Olympic-sized swimming pool")
Result: Wolfram|Alpha did not understand your input

Thought: Wolfram|Alpha is not providing the information I need. I'll try searching the web for the dimensions of an Olympic-sized swimming pool.
Action: read_webpage("https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Olympic-size_swimming_pool#Dimensions")
Result: web page too long

Thought: I'm having trouble finding the dimensions of an Olympic-sized swimming pool. I'll try a different approach and search for the volume of a standard swimming pool.
Action: search_wolfram("volume of a standard swimming pool in cubic meters")
Result: Wolfram|Alpha did not understand your input

Thought: I'm having trouble finding the volume of a swimming pool. I'll try searching the web for the volume of a standard swimming pool.
Action: read_webpage("https://www.swimuniversity.com/pool-volume-calculator/")
Result: web page too long

Thought: I'm having trouble finding the volume of a swimming pool. I'll try a different approach and ask the user for the dimensions of the swimming pool.
Action: ask_question("Can you provide the dimensions (length, width, and depth) of the industrial-sized swimming pool you have in mind?")
Result: I dont know can you search the web

Thought: The user wants me to search the web for the dimensions of an industrial-sized swimming pool. I'll try again.
Action: read_webpage("https://www.riverpoolsandspas.com/blog/inground-pool-sizes")
Result: Error while fetching and parsing web page: Request failed with status code 404

Thought: The web page I tried to access returned a 404 error. I'll try searching for the dimensions of a standard swimming pool instead.
Action: read_webpage("https://www.poolpricer.com/standard-pool-sizes/")
Result: Error while fetching and parsing web page: Request failed with status code 404

Thought: I'm having trouble finding information on swimming pool dimensions. I'll try a different approach and search for the dimensions of a large swimming pool.
Action: read_webpage("https://www.dimensions.guide/element/swimming-pools")
Result: Error while fetching and parsing web page: Request failed with status code 404

Thought: I'm having trouble finding information on swimming pool dimensions. I'll try a different approach and search for the dimensions of a commercial swimming pool.
Action: read_webpage("https://www.poolandspa.com/page596.htm")
Result: Error while fetching and parsing web page: unable to verify the first certificate

Thought: I'm having trouble finding information on swimming pool dimensions. I'll try a different approach and search for the dimensions of a large swimming pool using a different search engine.
Action: read_webpage("https://www.dimensions.com/collection/swimming-pools")
Result: Error while fetching and parsing web page: Request failed with status code 404

Thought: I'm having difficulty finding information on swimming pool dimensions. I'll try one more time to search for the dimensions of a large swimming pool.
Action: read_webpage("https://www.swimmingpool.com/blog/what-are-the-different-pool-sizes/")
Result: Error while fetching and parsing web page: Request failed with status code 403

Thought: I'm unable to find information on swimming pool dimensions. I'll inform the user that I'm unable to answer their question.
Action: finish("I'm sorry, but I'm unable to find the information needed to answer your question about filling an industrial-sized swimming pool with candy canes.")
